# Coding Standards and Conventions

## Project Structure

- Controllers go in [app/controller/](mdc:app/controller)
- Models go in [app/model/](mdc:app/model)
- Views go in [view/](mdc:view)
- Routes are defined in [route/](mdc:route)
- Configuration files go in [config/](mdc:config)

## Naming Conventions

- Controllers: PascalCase, suffixed with `Controller`
- Models: PascalCase, singular form
- Views: lowercase with underscores
- Config files: lowercase with hyphens
- Routes: lowercase with hyphens

## Code Style

This project follows PSR-12 coding standards. Key points:
- Use 4 spaces for indentation
- Use UTF-8 encoding for PHP files
- Files MUST use only <?php and <?= tags
- Class names MUST be declared in PascalCase
- Method names MUST be declared in camelCase
- Constants MUST be declared in all upper case with underscore separators

## Documentation

- All classes should have PHPDoc blocks
- All public methods should be documented
- Complex logic should include inline comments
- API endpoints should be documented in the controller methods

